  "title": "HEMOGLOBINAS INESTABLES Y HEMOGLOBINAS CON AFINIDAD ALTERADA POR EL OXÍGENO",
  "guid": "2F8F55B76035D9413F3F4178",
  "filepath": "/sessions/bold-jolly-cerf/mnt/Dropbox/- Esquemas/- Entidades clínicas/Cardiología/Williams. HEMOGLOBINAS INESTABLES Y HEMOGLOBINAS CON AFINIDAD ALTERADA POR EL OXÍGENO-2025-1.smmx",
  "root": {
    "id": "0",
    "parent": "-1",
    "text": "HEMOGLOBINAS INESTABLES Y\nHEMOGLOBINAS CON AFINIDAD ALTERADA\nPOR EL OXÍGENO",
    "guid": "WmaNdgcZRSJSfN58buYQpQ",
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "1",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "##\nHEMOGLOBINAS\nINESTABLES",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "2",
            "parent": "1",
            "text": "### Definición",
            "guid": "WcnWSktonFMQccAfS5RXfw",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "3",
                "parent": "2",
                "text": "- Producidas por mutaciones que cambian secuencia de aminoácidos → inestabilidad y precipitación",
                "guid": "BJpSUgDj8rdO1fazR_LdiA",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "4",
                "parent": "2",
                "text": "- Homotetrámeros de cadenas β (HbH) o γ (Hb Bart) también son inestables (presentes en α-talasemia)",
                "guid": "BxglUFy6EoU73V_ff7KQEw",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "5",
            "parent": "1",
            "text": "### Etiología y\npatogenia",
            "guid": "RwNNv1XeTnlLCcxlcHlahQ",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "6",
                "parent": "5",
                "text": "- Interacciones no covalentes mantienen estructura del tetrámero de Hb",
                "guid": "OTR_vjxDonoagMswcvmgqA",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "7",
                "parent": "5",
                "text": "- Sustituciones o indeles debilitan interacciones → desnaturalización → precipitación → cuerpos de Heinz",
                "guid": "a9L4MXq2pHEyOOIgRjmFpw",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "8",
                "parent": "5",
                "text": "- Cuerpos de Heinz alteran deformabilidad al unirse al citoesqueleto → dificultad para pasar por senos esplénicos",
                "guid": "Ac_pkwS1wJw1H5ZMB4wzKg",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "9",
                "parent": "5",
                "text": "- \"Deshuesado\" de cuerpos de Heinz → pérdida de membrana → destrucción eritrocitaria → anemia hemolítica",
                "guid": "J-hIMmGp08FWqHoyAbIefA",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "10",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Herencia",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "11",
            "parent": "10",
            "text": "- Autosómica dominante",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "12",
            "parent": "10",
            "text": "- Individuos afectados: heterocigotos\n(combinación de HbA y Hb inestable)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "13",
            "parent": "10",
            "text": "- No existen homocigotos ni heterocigotos\ncompuestos (probablemente letales)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "14",
            "parent": "10",
            "text": "- >80% de casos:\ndefectos en cadena β",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "15",
            "parent": "10",
            "text": "- Defectos en cadena α menos\nproblemáticos (4 genes α disponibles)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "16",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Datos clínicos",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "17",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Hemólisis: reticulocitosis,\nbilirrubina indirecta alta, LDH alta,\nhaptoglobina baja o nula",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "18",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Hemólisis\ngeneralmente\ncompensada",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "19",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Fármacos oxidantes pueden\nprecipitar hemólisis",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "20",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Manifestación según\ncadena afectada:",
            "guid": "",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "21",
                "parent": "20",
                "text": "- Mutaciones β: hemólisis post-periodo\nneonatal (tras reemplazo de HbF)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "22",
                "parent": "20",
                "text": "- Mutaciones α: hemólisis\ndesde nacimiento",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "23",
                "parent": "20",
                "text": "- Mutaciones γ: hemólisis\ntransitoria neonatal",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "24",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Hallazgos físicos: palidez,\nictericia, esplenomegalia",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "25",
            "parent": "16",
            "text": "- Orina oscura (catabolismo de grupos\nhem o cuerpos de Heinz)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "26",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Datos de laboratorio",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "27",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Concentración\nintracelular de Hb\nvariable",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "28",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Hb sérica normal\no disminuida",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "29",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Frotis: hipocromía,\npoiquilocitosis, policromasia,\nanisocitosis, cuerpos de Heinz",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "30",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Cuerpos de Heinz\nfrecuentes tras\nesplenectomía",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "31",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Reticulocitosis desproporcionada\na gravedad de anemia",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "32",
            "parent": "26",
            "text": "- Pruebas diagnósticas:",
            "guid": "",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "33",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Precipitación con isopropanol\n(sensible pero no específica)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "34",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Desnaturalización con\ncalor (específica)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "35",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Detección de cuerpos de\nHeinz (tinción supravital)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "36",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Electroforesis\n(utilidad limitada)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "37",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- HPLC fase inversa (para\nalgunas variantes)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "38",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Determinación de afinidad\npor oxígeno (P₅₀O₂)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "39",
                "parent": "32",
                "text": "- Análisis de DNA para\nidentificar mutación específica",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "40",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Diagnóstico\ndiferencial",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "41",
            "parent": "40",
            "text": "- Anemia hemolítica no\nesferocítica hereditaria",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "42",
            "parent": "40",
            "text": "- Falsos positivos en prueba de\nisopropanol: HbS,\nmetahemoglobinemia, HbF alta",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "43",
            "parent": "40",
            "text": "- HbH y Hb Bart (inestables, confirmables\npor pruebas de α-talasemia)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "44",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Tratamiento",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "45",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Evolución\ngeneralmente\nbenigna",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "46",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Cálculos biliares\nfrecuentes →\ncolecistectomía",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "47",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Episodios hemolíticos por\nfármacos oxidativos o infecciones",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "48",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Generalmente no requiere\ntratamiento específico",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "49",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Ácido fólico (beneficio\nno demostrado)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "50",
            "parent": "44",
            "text": "- Esplenectomía útil en algunos\ncasos (riesgo de infección por\nbacterias encapsuladas)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "51",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "## HEMOGLOBINAS CON AFINIDAD\nALTERADA POR EL OXÍGENO",
        "guid": "",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "id": "52",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Etiología y\npatogenia",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "53",
            "parent": "52",
            "text": "- Mutaciones en áreas cruciales\nalteran afinidad por oxígeno:",
            "guid": "",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "54",
                "parent": "53",
                "text": "- Estabilización estado T (tenso,\ndesoxi) → baja afinidad →\ncianosis/anemia leve",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "55",
                "parent": "53",
                "text": "- Estabilización estado R (relajado, oxi)\no desestabilización estado T → alta\nafinidad → eritrocitosis",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "56",
            "parent": "52",
            "text": "- Alteración unión 2,3-BPG a globinas\n→ afinidad alta por oxígeno",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "57",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "###\nCaracterísticas\nclínicas",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "58",
            "parent": "57",
            "text": "- Trastornos\nautosómicos\ndominantes",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "59",
            "parent": "57",
            "text": "- Asintomáticos si no reciben\ntratamiento inapropiado",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "60",
            "parent": "57",
            "text": "- Variantes con\nbaja afinidad:",
            "guid": "",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "61",
                "parent": "60",
                "text": "- Anemia compensada sin síntomas\n(mayor liberación de O₂)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "62",
                "parent": "60",
                "text": "- Saturación Hb disminuida sin\ndefecto cardiopulmonar",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              },
              {
                "id": "63",
                "parent": "60",
                "text": "- Eritropoyetina normal\n(aporte O₂ tisular normal)",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "64",
            "parent": "57",
            "text": "- Variantes con\nalta afinidad:",
            "guid": "",
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "65",
                "parent": "64",
                "text": "- Asintomáticos excepto si reciben\nflebotomía inapropiada para eritrocitosis",
                "guid": "",
                "children": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "66",
        "parent": "0",
        "text": "### Diagnóstico",
        "guid": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "67",
            "parent": "66",
            "text": "- Determinación del P₅₀ en curva\nde disociación Hb-O₂",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "68",
            "parent": "66",
            "text": "- Solo 50% detectables\npor electroforesis",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "69",
            "parent": "66",
            "text": "- Puede calcularse con sangre\nvenosa (pH, PO₂, saturación)",
            "guid": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
